'''Mihály Horváth''' (20 October 1809, [[Szentes]] – 19 August 1878, [[Karlovy Vary|Karlsbad]]) was a [[Hungarian people|Hungarian]] Roman Catholic bishop, historian, and politician. He was an exponent of Hungarian nationalism with an emphasis on its historical culture.

