{{Infobox journal | title = The Journal of Hellenic Studies | cover = The Journal of Hellenic Studies.gif | editor = Roger Brock | discipline = [[Hellenic studies]] | former_names = | abbreviation = J. Hellenic Stud. | publisher = [[Cambridge University Press]] on behalf of the [[Society for the Promotion of Hellenic Studies]] | country = United Kingdom | frequency = Annually | history = 1880–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayJournal?jid=JHS | link1 = http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayIssue?jid=JHS&tab=currentissue | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayBackIssues?jid=JHS | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = 00754269 | OCLC = 436724650 | LCCN = 09020515 | CODEN = | ISSN = 0075-4269 | eISSN = 2041-4099 }} '''''The Journal of Hellenic Studies''''' is a [[peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering research in [[Hellenic studies]]. It also publishes [[Book review|reviews]] of recent books of importance to Hellenic studies. It was established in 1880 and is published annually by [[Cambridge University Press]] on behalf of the [[Society for the Promotion of Hellenic Studies]]. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Roger Brock ([[University of Edinburgh]]).
