'''Unit 180''' is a [[North Korea]]n [[cyberwarfare]] cell, a component of the [[Reconnaissance General Bureau]].<ref name="Reuters">{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-cyber-northkorea-exclusive-idUSKCN18H020 |title=Exclusive: North Korea's Unit 180, the cyber warfare cell that worries the West |first1=Ju-min |last1=Park |first2=James |last2=Pearson |publisher=[[Reuters]] |editor-first=Raju |editor-last=Gopalakrishnan |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170521121302/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-cyber-northkorea-exclusive-idUSKCN18H020 |archive-date=May 21, 2017}}</ref>

Kim Heung-kwang, a former [[computer science]] professor in North Korea, stated that Unit 180 is likely involved in [[North Korea's illicit activities|illicit operations to obtain cash for the regime]], such as a [[Bangladesh Bank robbery|counterattack on Bangladesh Bank]] and the [[WannaCry ransomware attack]].<ref name="Reuters"/>

